===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Coming [[next]], either in [[sequence]] or in [[time]].
#: {{ux|en|See the '''following''' section.}}
#* '''1835''', Sir {{w|John Ross (Arctic explorer)|John Ross}}, Sir {{w|James Clark Ross}}, ''[http://books.google.com.au/books?id=SdQBAAAAYAAJ Narrative of a Second Voyage in Search of a North-west Passage &hellip;, Volume 1]'', pp.284-5
#*: Towards the '''following''' morning, the thermometer fell to 5&deg;; and at daylight, there was not an atom of water to be seen in any direction.
# About to be [[specified]].
#: {{ux|en|The '''following''' words have no definition{{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|of a wind}} [[blowing|Blowing]] in the [[direction]] of [[travel]].
#: {{ux|en|The '''following''' wind sped us on our way.}}

====Usage notes====
(Senses 1, 2) When it modifies a noun phrase, it is generally preceded by the definite article ''[[the]]'', and the combination functions as a [[determiner]] rather than a simple adjective. You can put it before a cardinal like ''the '''following''' two remarks'' instead of ''the two following remarks''.

